OF
ENERGY
STORAGE
THE
TEMPERATURE
JUMP
EFFECTS
ARE
FOUND
TO
DOMINATE
THE
INTERFACE
SOLIDS
TEMPERATURE
TIME
HISTORY
WITH
RELAXATION
EFFECTS
PLAYING
A
VERY
SECONDARY
ROLE
THE
THEORETICAL
RESULTS
ARE
COMPARED
WITH
SOME
EXPERIMENTAL
